On August 6, 1945, at about 8:15am local time, the US aircraft Enola Gay dropped an untested atomic bomb nicknamed "Little Boy" over Hiroshima. 

The explosion killed 70,000 people instantly and by December, the death toll rose to some 140,000 https://t.co/j9WLD7JXFc https://t.co/ZzJr4qjtnP

name: AJEnglish
text:
Japan was a fierce enemy of the US and its allies, Britain, China and the Soviet Union during World War II. 

In 1945, US & allies demanded the surrender of Japan. Shortly after, Hiroshima was attacked because it was seen as a "strategically sound" target https://t.co/j9WLD7JXFc https://t.co/mNHSghhMS0

name: AJEnglish
text:
After the bomb obliterated Hiroshima, the Japanese did not surrender.

Three days later, the US launched another mission and "Fat Man" was dropped over Nagasaki on August 9, 1945, instantly killing at least 40,000 people https://t.co/j9WLD7JXFc https://t.co/3qkjQGtwot
